# Security & Validation

## Strict URL Validation
Use `wp_parse_url()` for proper validation:
```php
// Before
if ( strpos( $url, 'youtube.com' ) === false ) return;

// After
$parsed = wp_parse_url( $url );
if ( ! $parsed || empty( $parsed['host'] ) ) return false;
$host = strtolower( $parsed['host'] );
return in_array( $host, array( 'youtube.com', 'www.youtube.com' ), true );
```

## Prevent Header Injection
Check for newlines in user input:
```php
// Before
$headers[] = 'From: ' . $name . ' <' . $email . '>';

// After
if ( strpos( $name, "\n" ) !== false || strpos( $name, "\r" ) !== false ) {
    return new WP_Error( 'invalid_input', 'Invalid input detected.' );
}
$headers[] = 'From: ' . $name . ' <' . $email . '>';
```

